				<pubDate>Wed, 26 Dec 2018 06:34:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Gabriel McQueen</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4558836</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There are over 2,000 species in the Lampyridae family (which should be capitalized; in scientific naming, only the species name is uncapitalized). It's unclear to me from your description whether 3757 all resemble one particular species of firefly, or whether they can have different appearances, resembling types within the Lampyridae.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
